==English==
===Noun===
'''series''' (''plural:'' '''series''')

#A [[number]] of [[thing]]s that follow on one after the other or are connected one after the other.
#A television or radio [[program]] which consists of several [[episode]]s that are [[broadcast]] in [[regular]] [[interval]]s
#:Friends'' was one of the most successful television series in recent years.''<!--note that the italicisation is correct here-->
#{{analysis}} The [[sum]] of the [[term]]s of a [[sequence]].
#{{cricket}} A [[group]] of [[match]]es between two sides; the aim being to win more matches than the opposition

====Synonyms====
*(''number of things that follow on one after the other''): [[chain]], [[line]], [[sequence]], [[stream]], [[succession]]

====Derived terms====
*[[arithmetic series]]
*[[geometric series]]

====Related terms====
*[[seriation]]
*[[serial]]

